      "message": "[Critical] Line 1992: 🔴 Critical Issues: body overwrite state is stored under the single shared key `pluginData[\"bodyOverwrite\"]`, but the plugin services are scoped per plugin and comments say unrelated plugins should not be affected. `clearBodyOverwrites()` clears that shared key for every loaded message in the conversation, so disabling or reconfiguring one plugin can remove another plugin\u0027s overwrite. Similarly, multiple active handlers overwrite each other in `transformSwarmMessages()`. Namespace overwrite data by plugin identity, or have the manager pass the calling plugin/handler id through update/clear/reload and only clear that plugin\u0027s key.\n\n```suggestion\nconst auto key \u003d fmt::format(\"bodyOverwrite:{}\", pluginId);\nmsg-\u003epluginData.erase(key);\n```",
