      "message": "Line 232: 🟡 Suggestion: `editMessageService` catches all `std::exception`s, logs them, and still returns success. Callers cannot distinguish a successful edit from a failed one, and validation failures for missing `body`/`edit` also return `0`. Return `-1` on invalid input or caught failures, and check `convModule()` before dereferencing.\n\n```suggestion\nconst auto bodyIt \u003d cm-\u003edata.find(CommitKey::BODY);\nconst auto editIt \u003d cm-\u003edata.find(CommitKey::EDIT);\nif (bodyIt \u003d\u003d cm-\u003edata.end() || editIt \u003d\u003d cm-\u003edata.end())\n    return -1;\nif (auto* convMod \u003d acc-\u003econvModule())\n    convMod-\u003eeditMessage(cm-\u003epeerId, bodyIt-\u003esecond, editIt-\u003esecond);\nelse\n    return -1;\n```",
