      "message": "Line 269: 🟡 Suggestion: `transformSwarmMessages()` holds `mtx_` while invoking plugin-controlled virtual code. Other paths in this patch explicitly avoid this because plugin callbacks may call back into `ChatServicesManager`; this path can deadlock or block all chat-service operations while a plugin performs slow work. Snapshot the eligible handlers under the lock, then invoke them after releasing it.\n\n```suggestion\nstd::vector\u003cChatHandler*\u003e handlersToTransform;\n{\n    std::lock_guard const lk(mtx_);\n    // populate handlersToTransform from active/allowed handlers\n}\nfor (auto* handler : handlersToTransform) {\n    handler-\u003etransformSwarmMessages(messages, accountId, conversationId);\n}\n```",
